      "content": "thanks, that's a lot better and feels much more high-end. i like the \"stability\" part. \n\nactually, looking at these two, i'm worried about the target audience. when you describe Oak Ridge, it sounds very safe and predictable, which is what wealthy families want. but with West End, even with the \"refined\" wording, it still feels like you're trying to convince me it's not chaotic. \n\ndo you think there's a reason why it's harder to describe urban, diverse areas like West End as just \"prestigious\" or \"exclusive\" compared to places like Oak Ridge? like, is there an inherent difference in how those neighborhoods are perceived in real estate?",
